description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you have an active interest in supporting people who are living in their home environment but have a variety of nursing needs? We currently have a number of substantive posts across Exeter South and West Cluster for Registered Nurses available hours range from 22.5 hours to 37.5 hours a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a registered nurse working in the community you will provide person centered care based on the holistic nursing assessment in order to plan, implement and evaluate nursing care. You will promote and support self-management and work with people to manage their long term conditions, prevent hospital admission, and support early discharge from the in-patient setting. The role also focuses on using and developing your clinical skills and supporting individuals at End of life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are exciting opportunities for you to develop your nursing career. You will work in one of our five Community Nursing Teams which is part of the wider Adult Health and Social Care team, as well as working with a wide variety of providers, to meet the nursing needs of individuals in their home setting or alternative residential settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in community nursing is desirable but not essential as full training will be provided and fully supported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in joining our happy team and wish to discuss further, please contact either : Bonnie Elworthy, Community Nurse Team Manager, Mobile 07500073857 or bonita.elworthy@nhs.net or Jane Killick, Community Nurse Team Manager, Mobile 07725216101 or jane.killick@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are: &lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
